What’s happening?

The user is working from home, so the mapped drives can’t reach the file server because the VPN is disconnected. The key clue is:

“The network path was not found”

Improved Resolution Steps

Connect to the user’s PC using Remote Support.

Open the VPN Client and verify it shows Disconnected.

Click Connect and wait until the VPN status changes to Connected.

Ask the user to open File Explorer and test one of the mapped drives.

If the drive still shows disconnected:

Open File Explorer → This PC.

Click ⋯ (See more) → Map network drive.

Enter the department’s UNC path (for example \\fileserver\department).

Check Reconnect at sign-in.

Click Finish.

Confirm the drive opens successfully.

Root Cause

The user was outside the corporate network and the VPN connection was not active, so the workstation could not reach the file server hosting the mapped drives.

Prevention

Instruct remote users to connect the VPN before accessing mapped drives. If available, enable auto-connect VPN for remote workers.

Lessons Learned

When a user reports “network path was not found” while working from home, check the VPN first before remapping drives.
